(146, 'Cheyne Walk Brasserie', 'uploads/resturant/1485889597990.png,uploads/resturant/1486226172117.png,uploads/resturant/1486226172723.png,uploads/resturant/1486226172465.png,uploads/resturant/1486226172105.png,uploads/resturant/1486226172550.png', '6', '', '51.4832575', '-0.1695088', '50 Cheyne Walk, Chelsea, London SW3 5LR', 0, 'Beautiful high-end Brasserie in affluent Chelsea sorroundings.\r\n\r\nUber-chic and modern brasserie and salon in a luxurious Chelsea riverside setting. At the centre of the Belle Epoque dining room is an open grill where much of the French Gourmet Cuisine inspired menu is prepared. Cheyne Walk is perfect for intimate date dinner moments as well as day-time outings with the family.\r\n\r\nOne last word: The perfect date night? Dinner and wine at Cheyne Walk followed by a romantic stroll on the Thames! \r\n\r\nOpening times:\r\n\r\nMonday\r\nDinner: 6.45pm - 10.30pm \r\n\r\nTuesday to Saturday: \r\nLunch: 12noon - 3pm\r\nDinner: 6.45pm - 10.30pm \r\n\r\nSunday\r\nLunch: 12noon - 3.30pm \r\nDinner: 6.45pm - 9pm ', 6, '26', '5,6,7,8,10', '5', '6', '12:00', '21:00', 7, '19:00', '22:30', 1, '12:00', '22:30', 2, '12:00', '22:30', 3, '12:00', '22:30', 4, '12:00', '22:30', 5, '12:00', '22:30', 6, 159, 1, '2017-03-16 17:05:47', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(147, 'Kishmish', 'uploads/resturant/1485886393972.png,uploads/resturant/1485886393513.png,uploads/resturant/1485886393315.png,uploads/resturant/1485886393251.png,uploads/resturant/1485886393562.png,uploads/resturant/1485886393201.png', '28', '', '51.4803321', '-0.1934276', '448-450 Fulham Rd, Fulham, London SW6 1DL', 0, 'Modern Indian restaurant serving up great curries with a modern twist.\r\n\r\nLocated in the heart of Fulham and a short walk from Fulham Broadway station and Stamford Bridge, this restaurant is a must for diners seeking that traditional curry experience with a modern fine dining twist.\r\n\r\nOne last word: Try the "Buffalo Vindaloo" - Laverstoke Park diced buffalo cooked in vindaloo masala, served with ghee rice.\r\n\r\nOpening Times:\r\nMonday to Sunday: 5:30pm - 11:00pm\r\n\r\n', 8, '9,10', '5,6,8,10', '5,6,8', '5', '17:30', '23:00', 7, '17:30', '23:00', 1, '17:30', '23:00', 2, '17:30', '23:00', 3, '17:30', '23:00', 4, '17:30', '23:00', 5, '17:30', '23:00', 6, 160, 1, '2017-03-13 09:17:21', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(149, 'The Shed', 'uploads/resturant/1485886555417.png,uploads/resturant/1485886555984.png,uploads/resturant/1485886555398.png,uploads/resturant/1485886555203.png,uploads/resturant/1486220783464.png,uploads/resturant/1486220783395.png', '5', '', '51.5089789', '-0.1938766', '122 Palace Gardens Terrace, Kensington, London W8 4RT', 0, 'Farm to plate restaurant and bar serving up the very best of British.\r\n\r\nDown to earth restaurant and bar in Kensington popular for its ''farm to plate'' philosophy. Meals and drinks are freshly prepared using the best of British ingredients from the family farm and vineyard in West Sussex.\r\n\r\nOne last word: "More than a shed - this place has a higgledy-piggledy charm" - Michelin Guide\r\n\r\nOpening times:\r\nMonday: 6pm - 11pm\r\n\r\nTuesday - Friday\r\nLunch: 12noon - 3pm\r\nDinner: 6pm - 11pm\r\n\r\nSaturday\r\nLunch: 12noon - 4.40pm\r\nDinner: 6pm - 11pm\r\n\r\nSunday: Closed', 6, '25', '8,9,10,11', '5', '4', '', '', 0, '18:00', '23:00', 1, '12:00', '23:00', 2, '12:00', '23:00', 3, '12:00', '23:00', 4, '12:00', '23:00', 5, '12:00', '23:00', 6, 162, 1, '2017-03-06 18:48:01', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(150, 'Nutbourne', 'uploads/resturant/1485886660290.png,uploads/resturant/1485886660856.png,uploads/resturant/1485886660264.png,uploads/resturant/1485886660727.png,uploads/resturant/1485886660424.png,uploads/resturant/1485886660258.png', '23', '', '51.4792518', '-0.1679757', '35-37 Parkgate Road, Battersea SW11 4NP', 0, 'Renowned relaxed and welcoming restaurant serving fresh British food and wines.\r\n\r\nNutbourne takes its name from our family farm and vineyard in West Sussex where we grew up learning about produce from the land, wine making and inspired cooking. Today we serve our own meats, local fruits and vegetables, South Coast sustain- able fish and, of course, our award winning range of Nutbourne wines - Galdwin Brothers.\r\n\r\nOne last word: Farm to plate style restaurant serving the best seasonal food and wines in a relaxed atmosphere\r\n\r\nOpening times:\r\n\r\nMonday: Closed\r\nTuesday: Friday 10am â€“ 12.30 past midnight\r\nSaturday: 10am â€“ 12.30 past midnight\r\nSunday: 10am â€“ 5pm', 6, '25', '7,8,9,10', '5', '4', '10:00', '17:00', 7, '', '', 0, '10:00', '23:30', 2, '10:00', '23:30', 3, '10:00', '23:30', 4, '10:00', '23:30', 5, '10:00', '23:30', 6, 163, 1, '2017-03-16 17:14:20', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(151, 'Rabbit', 'uploads/resturant/1485886928850.png,uploads/resturant/1485886928180.png,uploads/resturant/1485886928996.png,uploads/resturant/1485886928550.png,uploads/resturant/1485886928486.png,uploads/resturant/1485886928751.png', '6', '', '51.488741', '-0.1660621', '172 King''s Rd, Chelsea SW3 4UP', 0, 'Farm to plate restaurant serving great British food and wines.\r\n\r\nOne of three restaurants by London''s most popular farmers. Meals are prepared using sustainable ingredients and wines from the family farm in Sussex are served in a bucolic space.\r\n\r\nOne last word: These guys invented the ''British tapas'' concept - Flair cooking, small plates, relaxed atmosphere loved by locals and travellers alike. \r\n\r\nOpening times\r\n\r\nMonday:  6pm - 11pm\r\n\r\nTuesday to Saturday: 12noon - 12midnight\r\n\r\nSunday lunch: 12noon - 6pm', 6, '25,38', '6,7,8,10', '3,5,7,8,11,12', '4', '12:00', '18:00', 7, '18:00', '23:30', 1, '12:00', '23:30', 2, '12:00', '23:30', 3, '12:00', '23:30', 4, '12:00', '23:30', 5, '12:00', '23:30', 6, 164, 1, '2017-03-17 12:21:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(152, 'Souk Medina', 'uploads/resturant/1485004273591.png,uploads/resturant/1485004273218.png,uploads/resturant/1485004273364.png,uploads/resturant/1485004273555.png,uploads/resturant/1485004273961.png,uploads/resturant/14', '8', '', '51.5129211', '-0.1221976', 'Royal Opera House, 1a Shorts Gardens, London WC2H 9AT', 0, 'London''s most popular Moroccan restaurant with generous food portions and an extensive ''shisha'' collection.\r\n\r\nArguably the most popular restaurant in London for North African gastronomic experience. Souk Medina boasts a very large, yet intimate venue for a truly unique dining experience featuring large food portions in a casual, relaxed and welcoming atmosphere.\r\n\r\nOne last word: ''Shisha time'' \r\n\r\nOpening Times:\r\n\r\nMonday - Saturday: 12noon to midnight\r\nSunday: 12noon - 11pm\r\n', 8, '21,22', '7,10', '5,6,8', '4', '12:00', '23:30', 7, '12:00', '23:30', 1, '12:00', '23:30', 2, '12:00', '23:30', 3, '12:00', '23:30', 4, '12:00', '23:30', 5, '12:00', '23:30', 6, 165, 1, '2017-03-07 11:33:55', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(156, 'Bellevue', 'uploads/resturant/1488818520103.jpg,uploads/resturant/1488818520269.jpg,uploads/resturant/1488818520861.jpg,uploads/resturant/1488818520750.jpg,uploads/resturant/1488818520503.jpg,uploads/resturant/1488818520931.jpg', '24', '', '51.4434644', '-0.1674757', '218 Trinity Rd, London SW17 7HP', 0, 'Beautiful French restaurant with a warm and homely feel, perfect for summer alfresco.\r\n\r\nSouth London''s new culinary haven in a glass-roofed greenhouse restaurant with country-style rustic decor. Bellevue comes as a great addition to the local culinary scene with exciting flavours and wines from across the channel.\r\n\r\nOne last word: A hot destination for â€œal frescoâ€ enthusiasts offering comfortable and tranquil terrace dining.\r\n\r\nOpening times:\r\n\r\nMonday to Sunday\r\nLunch: 12noon - 3pm\r\nDinner: 6pm - 10.30pm', 8, '26', '6,8,10', '5', '4', '12:00', '22:00', 7, '12:00', '22:00', 1, '12:00', '22:00', 2, '12:00', '22:00', 3, '12:00', '22:00', 4, '12:00', '22:00', 5, '12:00', '22:00', 6, 169, 1, '2017-03-06 17:38:08', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(160, 'Afternoon Tea Bus Tour', 'uploads/resturant/1485035854554.png,uploads/resturant/1485035854776.png,uploads/resturant/1485035854371.png,uploads/resturant/1485035854622.png,uploads/resturant/1485035854877.png,uploads/resturant/1485889335944.png', '33', '', '51.4924786', '-0.1483289', 'Victoria Coach Station, London SW1W 9TP', 0, 'Delightful afternoon tea bus tours.\r\n\r\nEnjoy an afternoon (or evening) of exquisite afternoon tea aboard this this vintage double decker bus as you take in some of the famous sights of London including The London Eye, Big Ben, The Houses of Parliament, Westminster Abbey, St Jamesâ€™s Park, Buckingham Palace, Hyde Park, The Royal Albert Hall and much more. An ideal experience for touring groups and romantic dates. \r\n\r\nOne last word: Due to UK laws, children under 5 would not be allowed on the Afternoon Tea Bus Tour.\r\n\r\nBuses depart from Victoria coach station daily at:\r\n12noon, 1pm, 2:30pm, 3:30pm and 5pm.\r\n\r\nBuses leave from 8 Northumberland Avenue daily at 12.30pm and 3pm.\r\n', 16, '33', '6,8,10', '5,6,7,8', '7', '12:00', '17:00', 7, '12:00', '17:00', 1, '12:00', '17:00', 2, '12:00', '17:00', 3, '12:00', '17:00', 4, '12:00', '17:00', 5, '12:00', '17:00', 6, 173, 1, '2017-03-28 16:56:14', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(163, 'Gaylord', 'uploads/resturant/1485040371342.png,uploads/resturant/1485040371618.png,uploads/resturant/1485040371408.png,uploads/resturant/1485040371976.png,uploads/resturant/1485040371252.png,uploads/resturant/1485040371818.png', '4', '', '51.5175875', '-0.14083', '79-81 Mortimer St, Fitzrovia, London W1W 7SJ', 0, 'Introducing one of London''s oldest and finest Indian restaurants in the heart of Fitzrovia.\r\n\r\nUpscale North Indian dining, with an imaginative menu and one of the country''s first tandoor ovens. Gaylord prides itself on serving the most authentic North Indian cuisine in London and has over the years been a top destination for the London celebrity crowd.\r\n\r\nOne last word: Stuff of legends, it is believed that the first ever Tandoor (charcoal clay oven) was lit right here in 1966!\r\n\r\nOpening times:\r\n\r\nMonday - Saturday \r\nLunch: 12noon - 2.45pm\r\nDinner: 6pm - 10.45pm\r\n\r\nSunday\r\nLunch: 12noon - 2.45pm\r\nDinner: 6.00pm - 10.30pm', 8, '9', '3,5,6,8', '5,8', '5', '12:00', '22:00', 7, '12:00', '22:30', 1, '12:00', '22:30', 2, '12:00', '22:30', 3, '12:00', '22:30', 4, '12:00', '22:30', 5, '12:00', '22:30', 6, 176, 1, '2017-03-16 17:22:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(178, 'The Gilbert Scott', 'uploads/resturant/1490719880448.jpg,uploads/resturant/1490719880810.png,uploads/resturant/1490719880732.png,uploads/resturant/1490719880297.png,uploads/resturant/1490719880179.png,uploads/resturant/1490719880513.jpg', '31', '', '51.5297503', '-0.1257503', 'St Pancras Renaissance Hotel, Euston Rd, Kings Cross, London NW1 2AR', 0, 'Another masterpiece from celebrated Chef Marcus Wareing serving up fine British cuisine and cocktails in elegant 5-star hotel.\r\n\r\nThe Gilbert Scott provides the ultimate grand dining experience, showcasing the finest British seasonal produce in the 19th century surrounds of St. Pancras Renaissance Hotel. A great choice for first dates and business lunches.\r\n\r\nOne last word: ''A celebration of the UK''s many regional and historic specialities'' - The Michelin Guide\r\n\r\nOpening times:\r\n\r\nMonday â€“ Tuesday:\r\nLunch: 12pm â€“ 2:45pm\r\nDinner: 5:30pm â€“ 9:45pm\r\n\r\nWednesday â€“ Friday:\r\nLunch: 12pm â€“ 2:45pm\r\nDinner: 5:30pm â€“ 10:45pm\r\n\r\nSaturday: 12:15pm- 10:45pm\r\n\r\nSunday (including bank holidays): 12:15pm â€“ 8:45pm', 8, '24,25', '3,5,6,7,8,11', '5,7,8', '6', '12:30', '20:30', 7, '12:00', '21:30', 1, '12:00', '21:30', 2, '12:00', '22:30', 3, '12:00', '22:30', 4, '12:00', '22:30', 5, '12:30', '22:30', 6, 191, 1, '2017-03-28 16:51:21', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(179, 'Tredwells', 'uploads/resturant/1490719374612.jpg,uploads/resturant/1490719374245.jpg,uploads/resturant/1490719374529.jpg,uploads/resturant/1490719374545.jpg,uploads/resturant/1490719374743.jpg,uploads/resturant/1490719374945.jpg', '8', '', '51.512282', '-0.1273413', '4a Upper St Martin''s Ln, London WC2H 9NY', 0, 'Iconic British restaurant from world-renowned Chef Marcus Wareing.\r\n\r\nWinner of AA''s London Restaurant of the Year, Tredwells creates contemporary British cooking in the heart of the West End. As well as high-quality food, two bar areas serving chef-inspired cocktails have helped build Tredwells'' reputation as one of the best venues in the West end.\r\n\r\nOne last word: Relaxed excellence in a neighbourhood dining room!\r\n\r\nOpening Times:\r\n\r\nMonday â€“ Thursday\r\nLunch: 12pm â€“ 3pm\r\nDinner: 5pm â€“ 10pm\r\n\r\nFriday\r\nLunch: 12pm â€“ 3pm\r\nDinner: 5pm â€“ 11pm\r\n\r\nSaturday: 12pm- 11pm\r\n\r\nSunday & Bank Holiday: 12pm â€“ 9pm\r\n', 8, '25', '3,6,7,8,10,11', '3,5,6,7,8,9,10', '5', '12:00', '21:00', 7, '12:00', '22:00', 1, '12:00', '22:00', 2, '12:00', '22:00', 3, '12:00', '23:00', 4, '12:00', '23:00', 5, '12:00', '23:00', 6, 192, 1, '2017-03-28 16:42:55', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(189, 'Chop Shop', 'uploads/resturant/1485985535765.png,uploads/resturant/1485985535739.png,uploads/resturant/1485985535899.png,uploads/resturant/1485985535451.png,uploads/resturant/1485985535397.png,uploads/resturant/1485985535772.png', '11', '', '51.5086087', '-0.1320914', '66 Haymarket, St. James''s, London SW1Y 4RF', 0, 'Extremely popular steak restaurant in a central London location.\r\n\r\nSpread over two floors and with an ersatz-industrial look, Chop Shop is a trendy and lively spot that would fit in nicely within Manhattan''s Meatpacking district. We recommend a cocktail to start with, then order ''jars'', ''crocks'' or ''planks'' of mousses, meatballs and cheeses; then on to our favourite - great steaks and chops!\r\n\r\nOne last word: How much do you l-o-o-o-v-e your stakes?\r\n\r\nOpening times:\r\n\r\nMonday to Saturday: 12noon - 12 midnight\r\n\r\nSunday: Closed\r\n', 6, '14,25,38', '6,7,8,10,11', '5', '5', '', '', 0, '12:00', '22:30', 1, '12:00', '22:30', 2, '12:00', '22:30', 3, '12:00', '22:30', 4, '12:00', '22:30', 5, '12:00', '22:30', 6, 202, 1, '2017-03-06 18:42:32', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
